# Routing Contract

The site uses **path-based routing**. URLs represent real pages that can be requested directly by browsers and search engines.

## Canonical routes

```
/                  → start page (loads first or featured artwork)
/works/<slug>.html → specific artwork
/all/              → list of all artworks (indexable list only)
/credits/          → credits and project information
```

## Runtime routing rules

The shared runtime (`app.js`) must determine the current route using:

```
location.pathname
```

Behavior:

• `/` loads the first or featured artwork from `registry.js`
• `/works/<slug>.html` loads the artwork module associated with that slug
• `/all/` renders the list of artworks only (no descriptions)
• `/credits/` renders the credits panel

## File structure

SEO wrapper pages correspond to these paths:

```
docs/index.html

docs/all/index.html

docs/credits/index.html

docs/works/<slug>.html
```

The wrapper pages exist only as **entry points**. Rendering is handled by the shared runtime.

Outcome:
Routing, SEO pages, internal navigation and sitemap generation all use the same URL model.

