# Task 3 — Add SEO metadata to artwork pages

Each artwork wrapper page must include unique metadata in `<head>`.

Required tags:

• `<title>`
• `<meta name="description">`

Example target:

Title:

"Blur Dots Shader — Generative Art"

Description:

"Interactive generative artwork where random dots accumulate with soft blur trails, built with WebGL and JavaScript."

Outcome:
Search engines display meaningful titles and descriptions in results.

---

# Task 4 — Keep `/all/` page as indexable list only

The `/all/` page must render only a list of links to artworks (no extra descriptions or paragraphs).

Outcome:
The page is indexable and stays minimal per UI rules.

---

# Task 5 — Add OpenGraph metadata

Add social sharing metadata to artwork pages.

Required tags:

• `og:title`
• `og:description`
• `og:image`

Outcome:
When links are shared in social networks (Telegram, Discord, Twitter, etc.), a preview card appears with title, description and image.

---

# Task 6 — Create sitemap.xml

Add a sitemap listing all crawlable pages.

Target file:

```
/sitemap.xml
```

Pages included:

• homepage
• artwork pages
• credits page
• all page (`/all/`)

Important rule:
The sitemap should eventually be **generated from registry.js**.

Outcome:
Search engines discover all pages quickly.

---

# Task 7 — Add robots.txt

Create crawler configuration file.

Target file:

```
/robots.txt
```

Minimal configuration:

• allow crawling
• reference sitemap location

Outcome:
Search engines understand crawl permissions and sitemap location.

